This paper deals with lower bounds on the weights of threshold gates, which are commonly studied in computational complexity theory and circuit complexity. The paper uses techniques from coding theory and information theory, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the study of Boolean functions and their representations, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the construction of lower bounds using combinatorial techniques, which could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
